{"questionId":"22461694","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The owner of the generator is suspicious of the switch manufacturer’s claims, so they look back through the past <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn></math> occasions when the switches were replaced. The records show whether no switches, one switch or two switches had failed.</p>\n<p>The data the owner collected are shown in the following table.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/e03ba9768b986c774ab6328cc24420731c20cf58.png\" width=\"510\" height=\"67\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\">\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A2</em></strong>\n</div>\n<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\">\n<strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>A1A0</em></strong> if one of the values is incorrect, <strong><em>A0A0</em></strong> otherwise.</div>\n<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></div>","meta":{"questionId":"22461694","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ1.4a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the values of a, b and c.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
